<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="ida8a9639e-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5" identifier="/us/usc/t10/s1172"><num value="1172">§ 1172.</num><heading> Enlisted members: during war or emergency; discharge</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">A person enlisted under <ref href="/us/usc/t10/s518">section 518 of this title</ref> may be discharged at any time by the President, or otherwise according to law.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="ida8a9639f-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5">(Added <ref href="/us/pl/90/235/s3/a/1/A">Pub. L. 90–235, § 3(a)(1)(A)</ref>, <date date="1968-01-02">Jan. 2, 1968</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/81/757">81 Stat. 757</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
</section>
